d valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Breaking new, Wierd Story!</span><hr size=1> Hey Horde,<br>
  New guy Tormek here.  Was reading your boards to get a feel for the guild.  Heres to hoping I get to join you.<br>
  As for Mrs Woolley, Im sorry for you loss.  <br>
  As for SONY, I think they're covered by rating EQ an its expansions as TEEN.  They choose to warn people that the game has violence, gore, and suggestive themes.  Aren't these three things the items that most parents don't want in movies?<br>
  I feel similarly as Hinelorf on this.  I've played this game 3 years.  I've read of players dieing on other servers.  Their guilds have memorial services.  Others are visited by their guildmates at their RL funerals.  Death happens.  There are ~400,000 players.  Of these people die every day.  On the server this kid came from, in his guild (if there was one) Im sure people are lamenting.  They are missing their friend as sure as some of us have in the past.  The woman who sued McDonalds, Mrs Woolley, and even Al Gore's campaign would all have us blame the world when we stub our toe.  I agreed with GW Bush then and I still feel it now -&quot;We need to put the blame where it begins, in the family.&quot;<br>
  Mrs Woolley is unique yes, because (IMO) she is unwilling or unable to take responsibility for the lifestyle of her son, for his mental health and growth while under her direct care, and come to terms with her grief for her son's death.  Mrs Woolley may also be striking out because she cannot presently get into her son's EQ world.  She may never get into her son's EQ world.  Because of this she may never know how her son's world / friends / time in EQ possibly supported, lightened, or yes even doomed him.<br>
  In this world we make our friends where we find them.  Be it in work, in a gym, or even behind a computer.  EQ is an extension of real life.  We have deaths, weddings, birthdays, and even births.  Im sorry for the death of a human being.  And Im sorry that Mrs Woolley can't except it.<br>
<br>
Peace<br>
<br>
Tormek <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/fhordeofshadows15583frm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=194.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/fhordeofshadows15583frm6.showNextMessage?topicID=194.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/fhordeofshadows15583frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=194.topic&index=0><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/fhordeofshadows15583frm6.emailToFriend?topicID=194.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/fhordeofshadows15583frm6.threadControl?topicID=194.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/fhordeofshadows15583frm6.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=194.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/fhordeofshadows15583frm6.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=194.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub94.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="hordeofshadows15583frm6">HoS General<option value="hordeofshadows15583frm7">HoS Applications<option value="hordeofshadows15583frm2">Hos Private<option value="hordeofshadows15583frm3">HoS Raids<option value="hordeofshadows15583frm5">Epi